name: Birgit Koenigsheim
title: Interim Manager & Coach, VP and MD in the Energy and Telecommunications Industry
summary:
Birgit is an executive digital technology leader with more than 20 years of experience across energy, telecommunication, IT and consumer domains.
In her current role as interim manager and coach she is driving strategic change and transformation programs for small and mid sized companies.
Previously Birgit has led the Services business as VP with full profit & loss responsibility at Schneider Electric. Beyond the traditional services of maintenance, modernization, customer training, network planning etc., Birgit was driving the path towards full digital services portfolio including consulting, preventive/ predictive services, remote support and AR-supported services based on the Schneider Electric EcoStruxure architecture.
Prior to this she held various leadership positions at Nokia and Siemens. During her career Birgit took over functions in product management, sales / technical sales, corporate development, management consulting, service management and automation, restructuring and major transformation programs.

Birgit has broad experience in setting up new business units & functions and organizational transformations on both, global and local level. She is an excellent communicator with recognized unique leadership skills, proficient at creating an environment that drives learning and entrepreneurial spirit.

Her background is Electrical Engineering (diploma) and she has spent multiple years outside of Europe in Australia, Russia and Myanmar.

Birgit is married and has two sons aged 18 and 15.
